# let's use a cell with Empire State Building
EMB_lon = 40.748460
EMB_lat = -73.985779
EMB_region = data[(data['west'] <= EMB_lat) & (EMB_lat <= data['east'])
                             & (data['south'] <= EMB_lon) & (EMB_lon <= data['north'])]
In [190]:

EMB_region.rename(columns={1230: 'value'}, inplace=True)
EMB_region = EMB_region.set_index(pd.date_range('05/1/2016', periods=int(24*31), freq='H'))

EMB_region['roll_value_12'] = EMB_region['value'].rolling(12).mean()
EMB_region['roll_value_24'] = EMB_region['value'].rolling(24).mean()

EMB_region['roll_value_48'] = EMB_region['value'].rolling(48).mean()
EMB_region['roll_value_168'] = EMB_region['value'].rolling(168).mean()

EMB_region['sin_value_6'] = np.sin(2*np.pi * EMB_region.index.hour/6)
EMB_region['cos_value_6'] = np.cos(2*np.pi * EMB_region.index.hour/6)

EMB_region['sin_value_12'] = np.sin(2*np.pi * EMB_region.index.hour/12)
EMB_region['cos_value_12'] = np.cos(2*np.pi * EMB_region.index.hour/12)

EMB_region['predictions'] = regressor.predict(EMB_region.drop(['value'], axis=1).fillna(0))
EMB_region['remains'] = EMB_region['value'] - EMB_region['predictions']
indecis = list(range(len(EMB_region.value)))[:]
indecis_weekends = list(i for i in indecis if EMB_region['is_weekend'].values[i])
indecis_mothersday = list(i for i in indecis if EMB_region.index.day[i]==8)
indecis_memorableday = list(i for i in indecis if EMB_region.index.day[i]==30)
plt.plot(indecis, EMB_region.remains[indecis], label='remains')
plt.plot(indecis_mothersday, EMB_region.remains[indecis_mothersday], label='mothersday')
plt.plot(indecis_memorableday, EMB_region.remains[indecis_memorableday], label='memorableday')
plt.plot(indecis_weekends, EMB_region.remains[indecis_weekends], label='weekends', alpha=0.4)
plt.xlabel('hours passed after 01.05.2016 (00:00)')
plt.ylabel('remains')
plt.title('Amount of taxi calls from Empire State Building cell (remains of linear model)')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

We can see all official USA holidays (Mother's day (08.05.2016) and Memorable day (30.05.2016))

Memorable day is Monday and it's lower than its mean, so let's count it in our model too

In [225]:
from itertools import product
D = 1
d = 1
ps = range(0, 8)
qs = range(0, 11)
Ps = range(0, 2)
Qs = range(0, 2)
parameters_list = list(product(ps, qs, Ps, Qs))
print('amount of different models: {}'.format(len(parameters_list)))

amount of different models: 352
In [226]:
%%time
results = []
best_aic = float("inf")
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')

for i, param in enumerate(parameters_list):
    try:
        model = sm.tsa.statespace.SARIMAX(EMB_region.value,
                                          exog=EMB_region[['is_weekend', 'roll_value_12',
                                                            'roll_value_24', 'roll_value_48',
                                                            'roll_value_168',
                                                            'sin_value_6', 'cos_value_6',
                                                            'sin_value_12', 'cos_value_12', 
                                                            'sin_value_16', 'cos_value_16',
                                                            'sin_value_24', 'cos_value_24',
                                                            'sin_value_48', 'cos_value_48',
                                                            'sin_value_96', 'cos_value_96',
                                                            'sin_value_168', 'cos_value_168',
                                                            'is_memorable_day']].fillna(0),
                                          order=(param[0], d, param[1]), 
                                        seasonal_order=(param[2], D, param[3], 24)).fit(disp=-1)
    except ValueError:
        continue
    aic = model.aic
    if aic < best_aic:
        best_model = model
        best_aic = aic
        best_param = param
    results.append([param, model.aic])
    print('{} out of {} '.format(i, len(parameters_list)))
    
warnings.filterwarnings('default')

Generally, model predicts well. It counts week seasons and some anomalysis (because of the regression features). But the prediction's lowest values are lower than the mean of the time series. The difference is not very big, but it can be a further problem. Maybe it can be because we've taken not real amount of (Q, P) in our SARIMA model
